tt executes its arguments under 'bash -c' after performing translations of words into characters or character combinations.
Use 'tt HELP' to display translations performed.

HELP 1|<N>
EXAMPLES
VERB|VERBATIM 	Skip translation of next word.

ACUTE                'Â´'
AMPERSAND            '&'
AND                  '&&'
APPEND               '>>'
APOSTROPHE           '''
ASTERISK             '*'
ATSIGN               '@'
BACKSLASH            '\'
CIRCUMFLEX           '^'
COLON                ':'

Example:
'ls -l /etc' => 'tt ls SPC DASH l SPC SLASH etc'
